bindingDesc.p:
Eighteenth or nineteenth-century full straight-grained red morocco;
                                double gilt fillet and inter-twined foliage and bars to form a
                                border; gilt-tooled board edges and turn-ins; marbled end-papers;
                                detached pink ribbon bookmark loose between leaves h7 and h8; four
                                raised bands to spine; gilt-tooled within compartments;
                                direct-lettered in gilt in second compartment: Petrarca; all edges
                                gilt; nineteenth-century gilt monogram of The John Rylands Library
                                (JR in roundel) stamped on front cover.
